Description:
Enviably Central with Big Block Potential
In the very heart of Airport West, this sixties-style home occupies an incredibly deep allotment (approx 843sqm) providing an instantly enjoyable family environment along with opportunities to build a new dream home or explore its exceptional development potential (STCA).
Immediately comfortable, the home's previously extended interior comprises 4 generous bedrooms (3 with built-in robes) together with a spotless central bathroom & separate WC.
Adding to its current appeal is a light-filled front lounge, kitchen with Belling oven & walk-in pantry as well as an adjoining dining area leading through to the versatile rear living room.
Other features include a gas heater & split-system air conditioner (both in the lounge), solid hardwood floors, NBN connection & a full-size internal laundry.
Outside, discover the home's main attraction - a simply enormous west-facing backyard garden complete with large storage shed, oversized single garage/workshop & additional carport via gated side driveway.
Walking distance to McNamara Avenue shops & cafes, local parks & sports facilities, it's also close to St Christopher's Catholic Primary School, buses & trams, Westfield Shopping Centre, Keilor Road restaurants as well as easy access to freeways.
Land, location and endless options - this is the one!

Description:
Family Favourite On The Park
Nestled in a quiet, family focussed neighbourhood abutting parklands, this smartly updated three bedroom single storey brick home is perfect for many stages of life. Proudly maintained and set on an easy to manage block, approx. 532m2, the property assures immediate enjoyment comprising spacious, light filled living room and open plan kitchen/dining zones spilling to an outdoor area ideal for entertaining. Smartly updated, the kitchen features a host of stainless steel appliances, modern counters and abundant cabinetry. A large fully renovated family bathroom and three comfortable bedrooms flow from a central hallway, including main with private powder room and his/hers built-in-robes. An extensive list of extras includes a gas heater, evaporative cooling, ceilings fans, polished floorboards, large laundry/storage and rain water tank. While plenty of off street parking is provided by wide driveway, carport with remote-controlled access and large steel garage with workshop/storage. All of this within a short distance from Keilor Central, schools, kindergarten, Green Gully Reserve, buses and freeways.

Description:
Fabulous Family Living - Walk to Victoria Uni
Perfectly arranged for fabulous family living, this spacious residence imposes its presence with dual living zones and splendid alfresco entertaining, complemented by a location brimming with lifestyle appeal.
Upon entry, stylish polished floorboards sweep along the entrance hallway to the rear of the home where the superb kitchen has been brilliantly configured to overlook the adjoining meals and family room, whilst enjoying the benefits of stainless steel appliances, including dishwasher plus a breakfast bench.
Spilling outside through glass sliding doors, a covered alfresco, paved entertaining zone and backyard provide the ideal space for hosting outdoor parties with family and friends, whilst a 2nd kitchen, accessed via the alfresco is ideal for those seeking to eliminate odours from the home.
Completing the entry level, you'll find a bedroom with built-in-robes, powder room and laundry. While the upstairs dimensions continue to impress with a family retreat opening onto a Juliette balcony, accompanied by three additional robed bedrooms, including the master suite boasting large walk-in-robe and floor-to-ceiling tiled ensuite, supplemented by a matching family bathroom and separate toilet.
Superbly appointed with ducted heating, evaporative cooling, alarm, under stair storage, satellite, water tank, garden shed plus a double garage with internal access.
Conveniently situated walking distance from parkland, St Albans shops, St Albans Train Station, St Albans Primary and Secondary, Victoria University (St Albans), close to Brimbank Shopping Centre, with nearby Western Ring Road providing easy access to the CBD.
Photo ID required at all open for inspections.

Description:
Your Piece of Australia
Summoning pure elegance with a distinctly modern flavour, this stunning residence offers exceptional living with no expense spared and combines picture perfect yards which are tucked in a private secluded locale enhanced over approximately 660sqm of land. Showcasing a well thought design with a mix of tones and textures throughout its sunken formal living to the generous open plan kitchen (with 40mm stone bench tops & waterfall, 900mm stainless steel appliances, dishwasher, fridge plumbing & glass splashback), meals and family. Generously offering four bedrooms, master with a WIR and ensuite, others fitted with built ins and serviced by the main bathroom and separate W.C.
A generous pergola stretches along side the home to meet the remainder yard creating a seamless indoor/outdoor flow ideal for all year round entertainment yet leaving plenty of room for the kids & pets to mingle on. Other features include, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, ceiling fans, dishwasher, LED downlights, frameless showers, ample storage, garden shed, alarm system, double garage with drive through access and much more. Refined and graceful, this complete home is positioned within walking proximity to Watergardens Town Centre & train station, schools & parks. Its sure to impress. Call now to arrange your private viewing.

Description:
Designer Style with Every Urban Advantage
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Please also register your interest to attend the auction so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations and be contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior.
Beyond the captivating Californian-inspired facade, this brand-new home delivers an executive family lifestyle of low-maintenance luxury with its flexible floorplan, premium inclusions and prime position with close proximity to the best of Airport West. High ceilings throughout, the home's lavish interior boasts four large bedrooms (alternate masters on each level), two deluxe ensuites, equally-stylish main bathroom with freestanding tub and guest powder room (fourth WC) - all with floor-to-ceiling tiles. Add to this a dedicated study (upstairs) and vast open-plan living/dining area accompanied by a gourmet kitchen complete with breakfast bar, Smeg appliances, first-class cabinetry and adjoining butler's pantry. Other stand-out features include split-system heating and cooling (living area, study and all bedrooms), alarm, concealed laundry facilities and excellent storage options, robes to all bedrooms, solid hardwood floors across both levels and stone benchtops throughout. Bi-folds from the living area reveal an outdoor deck with pergola and private back garden plus the added appeal of a carport and additional driveway parking space. A short stroll to McNamara Avenue shops and cafes, local parks and sports facilities, it's also close to Etzel Street buses and Matthews Avenue trams, St Christopher's Catholic Primary School, Westfield Shopping Centre and easy freeway access.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance.
Thank you.

Description:
Under Offer
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Surrounded by established gardens on an elevated corner allotment, this distinctive two-storey home delivers an exceptional family lifestyle with its versatile floorplan, long list of features and fabulous living/entertaining areas both inside and out. Impeccably-presented and bathed in natural light, the home's impressive interior comprises four main bedrooms (extra-large master with WIR) and home office/fifth bedroom, deluxe ensuite and two additional bathrooms - all with floor-to-ceiling tiles. Dual living zones include a spacious lounge with vaulted ceilings and expansive open-plan living/dining area accompanied by a superb stone-bench kitchen with soft-close cabinetry, ample cupboard space, dishwasher and Smeg cooking appliances. Along with ducted heating and refrigerated cooling throughout, this remarkable home also includes ducted vacuum, alarm and video intercom, square-set ceilings and solid timber floors, full-size laundry and under-stair storage space. Stacker doors reveal a wonderfully private backyard with brick-paved entertaining area and outdoor spa with waterfall, additional entertaining deck, established gardens and fruit trees, two-car off-street parking, plus a fabulous rooftop terrace to relax and enjoy the breathtaking city skyline views. Rachelle Road buses on the next corner, it's also close to the area's popular primary and secondary schools including St Bernard' College and PEGS, local parks and Steele Creek trails, Dinah Parade and Centreway shops and eateries, as well as easy access to the Calder Freeway.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance.
Thank you.

Description:
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST - CLOSES 26TH MAY AT 5PM
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Ideally situated in one of Keilor East's most sought-after pockets, this modern home presents an exceptional easy-living lifestyle opportunity with its free-flowing design, quality appointments and low-maintenance surrounds. Flawless presentation from start to finish, the home's versatile interior comprises three bedrooms (large master with WIR) complemented by a deluxe ensuite and equally-stylish main bathroom - both with floor-to-ceiling tiles. Add to this a dedicated study or sitting room, spacious and light-filled open living/dining area together with a tastefully-appointed kitchen complete with breakfast bar, soft-close cabinetry, walk-in pantry and stainless steel appliances. High square-set ceilings throughout, the home also includes a full-size laundry with large linen cupboards, ducted heating and evaporative cooling, plantation shutters, stone benchtops and solid hardwood floors. Double sliding doors lead out to the rear courtyard with extensive paving and high fences for added privacy, plus a remote-control garage with internal entry and additional driveway parking space. Walking distance to the open spaces of Rosehill Park, Phillip Road/Buckley Street buses and Milleara Shopping Centre, it's also close to popular primary and secondary schools (including PEGS and St Bernard's College), as well as easy freeway access.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance.
Thank you.
